description: For sale: $250,000. Nearly 3/4-acre secluded and picturesque wooded setting in the heart of vibrant St. Paul.  This tranquil setting offers a new owner many opportunities.  Create an abundant garden in which to grow your own produce.  Chef inspired modern kitchen w/duel fuel range and ample storage featuring comfort pull out shelving.  Relax in the inviting Knotty Pine paneled living room featuring cozy wood burning stove. Admire the beauty of changing seasons and abundant wildlife, viewed through a bank of French windows.  Enjoy the feeling of being "up north at a cabin" with the warm wood tones and maple flooring.  Freshly painted generously sized bedrooms. One offering new carpeting w/access to an unfinished attic space for potential expansion. Second w/bird's eye maple flooring and access to a potential roof top porch. Many add'l updates. Conveniently located for work, education, entertainment, dining and boutique shops. Minutes from Mississippi River Rec. Area and Metro Bike Trail.  A SPEICAL MESSAGE FROM THE SELLER:"Having a home in the middle of the city with a beautiful expansive yard that I would garden, watch birds and wildlife, plus relax with privacy, was a gift. As an artist, I would paint in the bright sunlit room that overlooked a tranquil and peaceful vista. Detached from the bustling city in my serene and secluded home, yet just minutes away from work, I enjoyed country living with the convenient commuting, great shopping, unique restaurants, fun events, concerts and festivals that Saint Paul has to offer. Best of both worlds!"

description: Recently sold: $255,000. This historic home was built for city founder Edward Phalen, and passed off to Edmund Rice... maybe you've heard of them; their namesakes (Lake Phalen and Rice Street) are just blocks away. This home retains natural woodwork, solid doors, hardwood floors, and very high ceilings. It has a huge yard, an unbeatable view of the city, and is reputed to be one of the highest points in St.Paul. It has an oversized, heated 3-car garage with pull-down stairs for storage. New driveway and patio (2018), siding (2016); real fireplaces (one with original, ornate stonework), 3 pellet stoves (main level, attic, garage). This property has been licensed for rental and is set up to be two independent units. The main entryway can be used to access the top and bottom units separately, and independently. Main level, there are 2 bed, a 3/4 bath, a 4-season porch, and a kitchen, living and dining room. Second level, 2 bed, full bath, kitchen/living, and full attic bedroom.

description:
Recently sold: $218,000. Great investment:  Duplex Up/Down.  Have help with your mortgage.  Live in one unit and rent out other. 

 Original hardwood floors built in buffets classic 1912.






 Easy access to Hwy 35E about 1 mile. 
 St Patrick's of St Paul Church and Community of Peace Academy School right across the street. 
Very soothing chimes from church tower at noon. 
 This property is in a  great location for a duplex.  
There are 5 bedrooms, 1 large and 1 small bedrooms on the bottom floor (unit) and 1 large and 2 small bedrooms on the top floor (unit).
 It is located in the Payne and Phalen part of St Paul.  
It has hardwood floors that gives it an old wood charm.  
It has a large unfinished basement.  
There are a lot of windows and 4 lead glass windows.  
The property is located on a large corner lot with a lot of storage area.  
The recent City of St Paul inspection was on March 11, 2019 which received an "A" grade.  The next inspection is in March 2025 the longest term by the City of St Paul 6 years.
Please have mortgage pre-approved letter in hand before making an appointment to view this home. 
 This home is sold by owner. 
 Buyer's agent will be compensated 2.5%. 
 Showing will be scheduled with proof of funds.  
Showing upper floor (unit) first.  If additional interest 24 hour notice is required for lower floor (unit) tenant occupied.
This is a great cash flow.  
Rents are below market rates with quite a bit of room for improvement.

description:
Recently sold: $230,000. This 1900's Craftsman Bungalow has been completely restored from top to bottom. Beautiful classic woodwork with original built in's and refinished hardwood floors. BRAND NEW quartz countertops, tile backsplash, custom cabinets, drop zone, and stainless steel appliances installed in kitchen. Fresh paint on the entire exterior and interior, new light fixtures and hardware, new water heater, beautiful new landscaping and re stained large shaded deck out back perfect for entertaining. Both bathrooms have been remodeled with all new timeless ceramic tile and an original clawfoot bathtub on main floor. Enjoy the city from your charming front porch or walk down to the delicious East Side Pizza for dinner. Just a bike ride away from Lake Phalen, easy highway access and very close proximity to downtown 
St Paul. You don't want to miss out on this amazing property! 1year home warranty will be transferred to the buyer at closing.

description: Recently sold: $246,400. Great 4-bedroom, 2-bath, 2-car, 2-Story built in 2002 in Saint Paul.  This home is a "Must See." Walking up to the home, you will find this to be the perfect place to relax on the large front porch (22x7). On the main level you will find a large, freshly painted living room (14x13) with new carpet.  Spacious kitchen with stainless steel appliances, oak cabinets, lots of counter top space which flows into the huge eat in kitchen/informal dining area (14x10). Newly remodeled ½ bath on the main level with new vanity and toilet.  Walking to the upper level you will find 3 spacious bedrooms, new carpet, laminate wood flooring in the landing area, flowing into the full bath room with new vanity.  The lower level is nicely finished with laminate wood flooring in the family room (15x14), six-panel doors, and new carpet in the 4th bedroom.  Enjoy the fenced-in yard with a detached 2-car garage (22x22).
